==English==
===Etymology===
In Latin ''Nekros'' means [[corpse]]
===Noun===
'''necromancy'''
#[[Magic]] involving the [[dead]] or [[death]]

Necromancy is derived from the Greek Necromantia. Necro(the dead) Mancy(witchcraft or magic). Many different cultures have used necromancy. There is therefore much controversy as to how it is used. There are two clear divisions of necromancy however, that branch in which one consults directly with the corpse or spirit, and that branch wherein one takes the spirit within oneself, thereby using its knowledge (usually to glean the future). Though many books or teachers  promise you they can give you this art, next to none can. To perform true necromancy find a corpse, and cut its head off. At the next darkening of the moon at four o-clock in the morning begin doing yoga, focusing on nothing but staying awake. When it comes for you (be assured that it will), breathe it in and hold it. Do not let it go till you have what you want. Make sure you rebury the head by the next dark of the moon.
